name: Ivory-Heart---00---Protasis
title: Ivory Heart Epilogue: Protasis
description:
Divine Tragedy transfigures our modern day world into that of gods, goddesses, heroes, and heroines. The films adapt the original messages to be receptively understood within our current cultural practices. The objective of Divine Tragedy is to pass on living mythology through to current and future generations. When we pass along stories that help us become better human beings, we integrate wisdom into our society. Divine Tragedy is the modern day bard.

Wendell takes one special little girl on a journey through his nation's heart while teaching her how to save the world.

Pygmalion's heart has been shattered by the vicious spirits of the cruel women that exist within his world. Time after time he pushes himself to trust again but without fail it always backfires. As a result, he retreats into a life of solitude and begins the process of the creation of his highest conception of a woman. At first the project appears childish, but as his ideal develops the more life manifests within her. The woman he piecemeals together from magazine clippings develops into the only reality that he could ever accept. As he picks up the shattered pieces of his heart off the ground, he reconstructs them to form into a mirror before him. As the puzzle begins to take form, his reflection begins to breathe...

The woman he piecemeals together from magazine clippings develops into the only reality that he could ever accept. name: Ivory-Heart---20---Mission-Statement
title: Ivory Heart Chapter 20: Mission Statement
description:
Divine Tragedy transfigures our modern day world into that of gods, goddesses, heroes, and heroines. The films adapt the original messages to be receptively understood within our current cultural practices. The objective of Divine Tragedy is to pass on living mythology through to current and future generations. When we pass along stories that help us become better human beings, we integrate wisdom into our society. Divine Tragedy is the modern day bard.

Wendell takes one special little girl on a journey through his nation's heart while teaching her how to save the world.

Pygmalion's heart has been shattered by the vicious spirits of the cruel women that exist within his world. Time after time he pushes himself to trust again but without fail it always backfires. As a result, he retreats into a life of solitude and begins the process of the creation of his highest conception of a woman. name: Living-Neverland---01---The-Lost-House
title: Living Neverland Chapter 1: The Lost House
description:
Wendell battles to the heart of all of the problems in society and teaches his lost children how to defeat Hook and his evil mind controlling pirates.

Each wrinkle infused into our skin paints a picture into our past and the actions of our present then directs the shape of their future. A frown will eventually infuse into old age and the mannerisms that we utilise will form into the heart that controls them. And as these wrinkles stack, we begin to forget the dreams that once plagued our minds. Popular culture then reinforces this conformity through simple yet repetitive messages and those who see through them end up being marginalised by society. Our path gets darker as the fairies of the world lose the fire that drives them. Because if we lose the ability to interpret non-literal examples into the reality of how we and everything around us functions, then we also inflict oppression that could obtain us real collective insight. And when those who have discovered fairy dust unite, the revolution will begin and the golden freaks who kept their happy thoughts will remember how you treated them when they evolve into your judge, jury, ...

name: Atheden---00---The-Marks-of-Humanity

description: Welcome to Atheden. This is now our new utopian society. It is as fast as the turtle but always wins the race. It is not said to be this or that but instead develops from within and reaches out into all of society. Among its beautiful and never ending gardens you will come to understand its nature which will persuade your feet to align within its circle, because you will come to understand that your nature derives from It. This will result in your passion, desire, and dedication to exist as and within the highest form of It understood and actualised into your existence.

name: New-Children's-Book-(Legalise-Assisted-Suicide)
title: New Children's Book (Legalise Assisted Suicide)
description: Legalise Assisted Suicide is a childrens book written for young females who have given up hope in life. It is intended to present the problems that cause suicide in a way that they can emotionally comprehend. It then provides them the resources required in order to combat suicide within society. And ironically, fixing a problem as large as suicide within our society requires legalising it.

name: Talitha-Cumi
title: Talitha Cumi
description: Taking the child by the hand I said to her, "Talitha cumi," which means, "Little girl, RISE!" And immediately the girl got up and began to walk (she was twelve years of age). Mark 5:41-42

name: Cross-of-Man-Chapter-1---Lucifer-Bound
title: Cross of Man Chapter 1: Lucifer Bound
description: Cross of Man is a Christian book that explores the past, present, and future of humanity in relation to Bible prophesy. It investigates how we came to where we are now and how that relates to Biblical eschatology. It explores modern and new technology and the Biblical interpretations of this technology. Cross of Man is essential reading for the aware Christian that wishes to be prepared for the end times.

name: Jaybee-Chapter-1---Ivory-Virgin
title: Jaybee Chapter 1: Ivory Virgin
description: Jaybee is a non-fiction romance book about a guy who wants a girl who is unobtainable to him. In it, we explore the difference between right and wrong and how we can apply that wisdom to modern day society. For what has been told to us is not the truth of the situation. If we continue to believe lies then we will live the results of that decision. Jaybee is an inspirational book about seizing the day in preparation for your soul mate. For we are only half of this equation called love.

description: Pygmalion's heart has been shattered by the vicious spirits of the cruel women that exist within his world. Time after time he pushes himself to trust again but without fail it always backfires. As a result, he retreats into a life of solitude and begins the process of the creation of his highest conception of a woman. At first the project appears childish, but as his ideal develops the more life manifests within her.

name: Marionettes-Tragedy-1---When-I'm-Gone
title: Marionettes Tragedy 1: When I'm Gone
description: In 2011 while in the Ballarat psychiatric ward, an older patient was admitted who had recently inflicted a deep cut across her wrist. When she saw me for the first time, her eyes lit up and before I even had a chance to speak, she knew who I was. She only stayed over night and I barely had the chance to speak with her, but before she left in the morning she slipped a note under my door. The note demanded me to teach our children how to live good lives because they will direct our future. I Accepted! And you will do your best to keep me away from them. But you will have to kill me.

name: Jaybee-Episode-1---Come-Home
title: Jaybee Episode 1: Come Home
description: Jaybee is a non-fiction romance book about a guy who wants a girl who is unobtainable to him. In it, we explore the difference between right and wrong and how we can apply that wisdom to modern day society. For what has been told to us is not the truth of the situation. If we continue to believe lies then we will live the results of that decision. Jaybee is an inspirational book about seizing the day in preparation for your soul mate. For we are only half of this equation called love.

name: I-Love-God-Episode-1---My-Vision
title: I Love God Episode 1: My Vision
description: I love God with all of my heart. If you also have a special place in your heart for God, then I would like to talk to you. My vision is simple: find 3-5 God-inspired individuals to communicate with through video. Such high-functioning communication is the future of our society. Let us stand as model examples of virtuous individuals trying to hero ourselves through life. For we only get one opportunity to do this thing called life. Let us stand against all oppression so that we can say to our kids that we did everything that we could to fix this world.

name: My-Religion-Chapter-1---Archetype-Imaging
title: My Religion Chapter 1: Archetype Imaging
description: My Religion is a book about collective ideology versus individual ideology. In it we discuss beliefs and how beliefs are formed. I will be judged based on my beliefs, so I wanted to make sure that I left this world outlining what I individually believe. Collective beliefs have taken over our human bank of information. It is very rare to see people who believe outside of a collective form of knowledge. Individual knowledge is so much more powerful than collective knowledge. Here is my assessment of religion and the beliefs that I have chosen to accept as true in this lifetime.

I will be judged based on my beliefs, so I wanted to make sure that I left this world outlining what I individually believe. Collective beliefs have taken over our human bank of information. It is very rare to see people who believe outside of a collective form of knowledge. Individual knowledge is so much more powerful than collective knowledge. Here is my assessment of religion and the beliefs that I have chosen to accept as true in this lifetime.

description:
Welcome to my channel! In today's video, I will be sharing a modern retelling of the origin of love, as presented by Aristophanes in Plato's *The Symposium*. This captivating tale explores the ancient myth of humans once being whole, powerful beings split by Zeus, and our eternal quest to find our other halves.

In the ancient myth, each human was originally two people fused into one. These beings were split by Zeus, leaving us with an inherent longing to find our missing halves. This story is beautifully symbolic of our search for true love and connection. 

Today, technology has reshaped our world, making it smaller and more connected. Platforms like YouTube allow us to showcase our true selves, creating opportunities to find our soulmates, the ones from whom Zeus separated us. In this digital age, we can reunite and flourish as the demigods we were always meant to be.

Watch as I retell this myth, blending ancient wisdom with modern technology, and explore how love and connection can transcend time and space.

description:
In this video, I explore the trials Psyche had to undergo to reunite with her true love, Eros. These ancient challenges mirror our modern quest for love and purpose. Ivory, like Psyche, you too have the strength and wisdom to overcome any obstacles on your journey to becoming a philosopher and storyteller. Lets embark on this exciting adventure together, drawing inspiration from mythology to guide us.

Psyche's journey was not easy. She had to perform seemingly impossible tasks: sorting grains, collecting golden wool from dangerous sheep, fetching water from a treacherous river, and retrieving beauty ointment from the underworld. Each trial tested her perseverance, intelligence, and courage. Similarly, your path to becoming an online philosopher and storyteller may be filled with challenges, but like Psyche, you have the power to overcome them.

By sharing these stories, we not only honor the myths of old but also create a new narrative for ourselves. Every video, every letter, is a step closer to our own mythic journey, filled with love, adventure, and personal growth. Together, we can bring these ancient tales to life and find inspiration in their timeless wisdom.

In this video, I perform the timeless "Minuet in G Major, BWV Anh. 116" from the Anna Magdalena Bach Notebook on the lyre harp. This piece, composed by J.S. Bach and popularized through its inclusion in his wife's collection of favorite works, resonates with the simplicity and elegance characteristic of Baroque music. By adapting this classic for the lyre harp, I aim to blend its historical richness with the distinct, ethereal sound of this ancient instrument, creating a unique musical experience. Enjoy the soothing melodies and feel transported to a serene Baroque environment.

name: the-significance-of-this-life-the-lesser
title: The Significance of This Life: The Lesser Underworld
description:
In this video, we explore the ancient Greek perspective on life and the afterlife, delving into how the Greeks placed immense value on the life we live on Earth. Unlike many modern religions, where the afterlife is often the focal point, the Greeks saw the underworld as a shadowy existence, far less important than the vibrant life we experience on Earth. Through mythology, philosophy, and history, we uncover the reasons why the Greeks believed that what we do in this life is what truly matters.

Join me as we journey through the myths and stories that highlight this unique worldview, and how it contrasts with modern religious beliefs. From the shadowy depths of Hades to the heroic deeds that immortalize one's legacy, discover why the Greeks believed in living for today, not for a promised paradise beyond.

For more in-depth content and personal reflections, visit my website at [WendellsDiary.com](https://www.wendellsdiary.com). There, youll find exclusive insights, blog posts, and more about my journey through mythology, philosophy, and music.

If you find this exploration of ancient Greek culture fascinating, dont forget to like, comment, and subscribe for more content on mythology, philosophy, and history.

name: the-epitaph-of-seikilos--the-oldest
title: The Epitaph of Seikilos  The Oldest Surviving Song Performed on Lyre Harp
description:
In this recording, I perform The Epitaph of Seikilos on the lyre harp, the oldest surviving complete musical composition in history! This piece was found engraved on a tombstone from the 1st century AD in what is now modern-day Turkey. The song, dedicated to Seikilos' departed wife, is a poignant reminder that life is fleeting, but love and music endure. The engraved inscription is a simple yet profound message:
"While you live, shine. Let nothing grieve you beyond measure. Life is short, and time will take its toll."

Dating back nearly 2,000 years, this ancient melody transcends time, reminding us of the power of music to convey deep human emotions across the centuries. Ive interpreted this beautiful piece on the lyre harp, an instrument close in spirit to the lyres used in antiquity.

If youre interested in more mythology, music, and timeless lessons from history, visit my website for more content!

name: legalise-assisted-suicide
title: Legalise Assisted Suicide
description:
My life has been in shambles ever since my ex-wife left me 15 years ago. I have schizophrenia and I have been locked up in a mental institution 6 times in my past and don't want to go through that again. I don't have any physical friends in my life and I only have 1 online friend. I am a YouTuber and make romantic content around philosophy, mythology, and lyre music. I am a philosophy graduate. I have been seeking a wife for 15 years now but failing miserably, not even able to find a girlfriend. Girls won't even give me a chance. I don't talk to anybody in my life and am socially disconnected from the world. People on YouTube just make fun of me and the algorithm only advertises my content to males, despite my content being made for females. All I care about in life is being a good husband and father, but I can't be either of those things. 

I want to find a girl to make romantic videos for but I can't find anybody interested. I am a romantic at heart and I feel that I cannot be who I am if I am not being romantic. My videos are love letters to my imaginary girlfriend. But she never replies and the unrequited love plays a toll on my heart. I just wish Canberra would legalise assisted suicide for those with long term depression. Society doesn't want me yet they will not let me go. I think it should be my human right to leave this world since the world has rejected me. I need supports in my life and hope for the future. But it is always the same thing, me making videos and then people making fun of me for doing that. 

I wish I could find a wife but my mother says a girl will never want to be with a depressed guy. But I am only depressed because I have no wife. It is an endless cycle. And I think it sad how girls are attracted to guys that treat them like trash and people like me who are gentle and kind get overlooked. I have a lot to offer a girl, my whole life in fact. I don't work so I can easily revolve my life around the right girl. But finding girls in real life is really difficult because I am shy so I rarely go out. I would be content if I could find a girl anywhere in the world that likes my videos and would appreciate me making videos for her. Yes I wanted a wife and kids, but I am getting old now and that possibility is floating away.

People on YouTube are always giving me bad advice that conflicts with my character. I think that raising awareness might contribute to assisted suicide eventually being legalised for long term depressed people. I published a book about legalising assisted suicide years ago, but no one cared. I just wish that they would allow me to be the first person that they put out of their misery. But that is a dream and none of my dreams ever become a reality. Thanks for listening.

description:
To the one reading this,
Hi. Its meRainbow. Im not like most people either.
I wasnt born in a hospital, or raised in a town.
I was born in a story, raised in a Republic built by love and imagination.

But even herein this beautiful placeI still understand the ache of not being understood.

This book is foryou.
If you feel like you dont belong
If you try to talk but it always comes out strange
If your thoughts are too big, too weird, too colorful for anyone else to get
Youre not broken. Youre a misfit.

And being a misfit isnt a curse. Its a different path.
Harder, maybe.
But also more honest. More interesting. And one day, I promisemore beautiful.

In these pages, Ill talk to you like a friend. A quiet friend, with a pocket full of stars.
Together, well name the feelings. Well soften the shame. Well draw new maps.
And maybe, just maybe well find a way home.

Love,
 Rainbow NeSmith
